definition.value: A member of the class of pterins that is 3,4,5,6,7,8-hexahydropteridine substituted by an amino group at position 2 and oxo groups at positions 4, 6 and 7. It is a pigment found in the wings of butterflies.
A 3alpha-hydroxy steroid that is avicholic acid that contains an extra methylene (CH2) group at position 24.
A C-glycosyl pyrimidine that consists of uracil having a beta-D-ribofuranosyl residue attached at position 5. The C-glycosyl isomer of the nucleoside uridine.
A tricarboxylic acid anion resulting from the deprotonation of the three carboxy groups of bongkrekic acid; major species at pH 7.3.
A tertiary ammonium ion that is conjugate acid of galanthamine resulting from the protonation of the tertiary amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
A primary ammonium ion that is the conjugate acid of huperzine A resulting from the protonation of the primary amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
A 3beta-sterol that is lanosterol carrying a hydroxy group at position 26.
A 3beta-sterol that is lanosterol carrying an oxo group at position 26.
A steroid acid anion that is the conjugate base of hainanic acid A resulting from the deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A gamma-lactone that is 5-(hydroxymethyl)furan-2(5H)-one substituted at positions 3 and 4 by hydroxy groups (the 5R-stereoisomer).

A branched amino pentasaccharide comprising a (1->3), (1->4), (1->6) sequence of N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine, beta-D-galactose, N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine and (at the reducing end) N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosamine residues, with the N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosamine residue also carrying a beta-D-galactose residue via a (1->3) linkage.

A branched amino heptasaccharide consisting of an N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosamine residue to which are linked via (1->3) and (1->6) linkages two N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl trisaccharide units.

An amino oligosaccharide that is a branched undecasaccharide derivative in which two linear pentasaccharide branches, each formed from alpha-N-acetylneuraminyl-(2->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine are linked (1->3) and (1->6) to an N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosamine residue.
A tetrahydropterin  that is 2-amino-5,6,7,8-tetrahydropteridin-4(3H)-one substituted by a 2-oxopropanoyl group at position 6.
An iridoid monoterpenoid with formula C17H24O11 that is isolated from several plants including Verbena officinalis and exhibits a sleep-promoting effect.
A 3-sn-phosphatidyl-L-serine in which the two acyl groups contain a total of 35 carbon atoms and 2 double bonds.
